    "Bakir-Gungor et al. (2021) utilized machine learning, specifically the RF method, to develop a classification model for Type 2 Diabetes (T2D) diagnosis and revealing that a subset of 15 commonly selected features had a significant impact on minimizing the microbiota required for T2D diagnosis, thereby reducing time and cost, showcasing the efficiency of ML in biomarker selection.",
    "(III) Biomarker discovery and patient subgrouping: Another study by Bakir-Gungor et al. (2022) aimed to identify biomarkers associated with human gut microbiota during IBD.",
